N2  - In the preceding paper, Schweiger extends the present authors' review of cognitive style measurement and finds fault with some of their classifications and descriptions. The present paper is a response to his criticism. It clarifies the original intentions and gives reactions to several of his other points. It closes by noting the significance of one's own cognitive style in dealing with the larger concerns of cognitive style measurement.
