T1  - Strategies Toward Political Pressures: A Typology of Firm Responses
AU  - Fischer, David W.
Y1  - 1983/01/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1983.4287665
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1983.4287665
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 71
EP  - 78
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Growth management strategies can fail, sometimes from lack of integrating political impacts into a firm's dominating market ideas. This paper outlines a set of responses for a firm confronted with external demands for change. The firm's product and its impact constitute a connected environment around the firm. Promotive thinking, seeing the product and impact environments as interdependent aspects in a political context and viewing impacts as new growth opportunities, can turn political pressures into an expansion of the market.
